(13, 82, 'WORLD TSUNAMI AWARENESS DAY', 'world-tsunami-awareness-day', '<h2 itemprop=\"name\" style=\"text-align: center;\"></h2>\r\n<p>What’s with the World Tsunami Awareness Day?</p>\r\n<p>The recent happenings in the Asia Pacific have led to a more increased awareness when it comes to hazards and risks being geographically located at the Pacific ring of fire and Pacific typhoon belt. Over the years, the new normal of disasters has led to increased damages and losses in the affected countries. Hence, there is a greater need for strengthened capacities and a built culture of disaster resilience<g class=\"gr_ gr_54 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Style replaceWithoutSep\" id=\"54\" data-gr-id=\"54\">.</g></p>\r\n', '\r\n<p><g class=\"gr_ gr_54 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_disable_anim_appear Style replaceWithoutSep\" id=\"54\" data-gr-id=\"54\">Did</g> you know that tsunamis are considered rare but are extremely deadly? Based on the UN Office for Disaster Risk Reduction (UNISDR) report, in the past 100 years, more than 260,000 people have perished in 58 separate tsunamis. This results in an average of 4,600 deaths per disaster which has surpassed the toll of any natural hazard.</p>\r\n<p>What is a Tsunami?</p>\r\n<p>A tsunami is a series of ocean waves that sends surges of water, sometimes reaching heights of over 100 feet (30.5 meters), onto land. It can kill or injure people, damage and destroy infrastructure facilities and can cause flooding and disrupt transportation, communication lines, power, and water supply. In other words, tsunamis can wipe out areas with these walls of water in a short time can lead to a widespread destruction in an area.</p>\r\n<p>Tsunamis are typically caused by large, undersea earthquakes at tectonic plate boundaries. Other causes of tsunami include underwater landslides and volcanic eruptions. When the ocean floor at a plate boundary rises or falls suddenly, it displaces the water above it and launches the rolling waves that become a tsunami.</p>\r\n<p>What is World Tsunami Awareness Day</p>\r\n<p>The World Tsunami Awareness Day is an initiative of the UN General Assembly to harness international cooperation in understanding risk reduction measures. The observance of the World Tsunami Awareness Day is set on every 5th of November. The date was chosen in honor of a true story from Japan: “Inamura-no-<g class=\"gr_ gr_42 gr-alert gr_spell gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim ContextualSpelling ins-del multiReplace\" id=\"42\" data-gr-id=\"42\">hi</g>”, which means the “burning of the rice sheaves”.</p>\r\n<p>During the 1854 earthquake in Japan, a farmer saw the tide receding, a sign of a looming tsunami. He set fire to his harvested rice to warn villagers, who fled to high ground. In the aftermath, he helped his community build back better to withstand future shocks, constructing an embankment and planting trees as a tsunami buffer.</p>\r\n<p>The 5th of November manifests that even in the past, people and communities were aware of the hazards and risks. And it is with community effort and participation that disaster resilience can be achieved.</p>\r\n<p>The true story of Inamura-no-hi is a reminder of the power of community participation and cooperation.</p>\r\n<p>The observance of the World Tsunami Day aims to increase tsunami awareness, to strengthen community participation and cooperation and to share innovative practices and approaches to risk reduction. This year’s theme aligns with the International Day of Disaster Reduction which aims at reducing direct disaster economic loss in GDP.</p>\r\n<p>The Philippines through the National Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Council will join the observance of the World Tsunami Day on November 5, 2018, and is set to conduct a tsunami drill in Pagadian City, Zamboanga.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Sources: UNISDR Report, National Geographic</p>', 1, 10, '2018-10-29 01:38:24', 413, '', '2018-11-08 03:41:59', 413, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2018-10-29 01:38:24', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{\"image_intro\":\"images\\/TSUNAMI.jpg\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"Tsunami\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"images\\/TSUNAMI.jpg\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":false,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":false,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":false,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"1\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_associations\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}', 11, 1, '', '', 1, 33, '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}', 1, '*', '', ''),
(14, 84, 'NDRRMC CONVENES IN PREPARATION FOR TYPHOON YUTU (I.N.)', 'ndrrmc-convenes-in-preparation-for-typhoon-yutu-i-n', '<h2 itemprop=\"name\" style=\"text-align: center;\"></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: #000000;\"><img src=\"http://ocd.gov.ph/images/OCD/PhotoRelease/PR1_1.jpg\" alt=\"PR1 1\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span>             </span>26 October 2018- National Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Council (NDRRMC) convened in preparation for Typhoon Yutu (international name) as it enters the Philippine Area of Responsibility (PAR) by 27 October 2018.</p>\r\n', '\r\n<p>            The Pre-Disaster Risk Assessment meeting was presided by NDRRMC Executive Director and Civil Defense Administrator Usec Ricardo B Jalad and attended by representatives from NDRRMC member agencies DSWD, DILG, NEDA, DOST-PAGASA, MGB, DepEd, PIA, DICT, NAMRIA, DBM, DOF, DPWH, PNP, BFP, AFP, and OCD CAR. The Regional DRRM Councils I<g class=\"gr_ gr_29 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Style replaceWithoutSep\" id=\"29\" data-gr-id=\"29\">,II</g>, III, IVA, IVB <g class=\"gr_ gr_28 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Punctuation only-ins replaceWithoutSep\" id=\"28\" data-gr-id=\"28\">and</g> V also joined the meeting via teleconference.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://ocd.gov.ph/images/OCD/PhotoRelease/PR1_2.jpg\" alt=\"PR1 2\" width=\"699\" height=\"465\" /></p>\r\n<p>             According to PAGASA, Typhoon Yutu (I.N. has maintained its strength as it continues to move West of the Philippines at 25 km/h with maximum sustained winds of 185 km/h near the center and gustiness up to 225 km/h and a diameter of 800 km. As reported, TY Yutu is expected to enter the Philippine Area of Responsibility 27 October 2018. Hoisting of Tropical Cyclone Warning Signal (TCWS) is expected over Eastern section of Northern and Central Luzon on 28 October 2018 (Sunday). TY Yutu is expected will bring moderate to heavy rains over Northern and Central Luzon starting 29 October 2018.</p>\r\n<p>            DENR-MGB added that possible landslides may be experienced in some areas in the Eastern section of Northern Luzon.</p>\r\n<p>            Agencies under the response cluster presented preparedness measure for TY Yutu. Among the relative measures is the issuance of warning and advisories to the Local Government Units by the DILG; DSWD’s efforts for the stockpiling of food and non-food items; the prepositioning and stockpiling of medicines and <g class=\"gr_ gr_33 gr-alert gr_spell gr_inline_cards gr_disable_anim_appear ContextualSpelling\" id=\"33\" data-gr-id=\"33\">medicine</g> supplies by DOH; AFP, PNP, BFP <g class=\"gr_ gr_31 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_disable_anim_appear Punctuation only-ins replaceWithoutSep\" id=\"31\" data-gr-id=\"31\">and</g> PCG have committed their response assets ready for deployment; and DPWH, DEPED <g class=\"gr_ gr_32 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_disable_anim_appear Punctuation only-ins replaceWithoutSep\" id=\"32\" data-gr-id=\"32\">and</g> DFA have activated respective units for the monitoring of the tropical cyclone.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://ocd.gov.ph/images/OCD/PhotoRelease/PR1_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"699\" height=\"465\" /></p>\r\n<p>             As of today, the NDRRM Operations Center is on <g class=\"gr_ gr_25 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Grammar only-ins replaceWithoutSep\" id=\"25\" data-gr-id=\"25\">WHITE</g> alert status and will raise its alert status to BLUE on 28 October 2018 in order to closely monitor the possible effects of the current weather system and ensure <g class=\"gr_ gr_26 gr-alert gr_spell gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim ContextualSpelling\" id=\"26\" data-gr-id=\"26\">efficient</g> coordination with the member agencies.</p>\r\n<p>             The public is being advised to monitor weather updates and bulletin provided by PAGASA. - End</p>', 1, 10, '2018-10-29 02:47:09', 413, '', '2018-11-07 01:42:35', 413, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2018-10-29 02:47:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":false,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":false,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":false,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"1\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"1\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_associations\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}', 16, 0, '', '', 1, 14, '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}', 1, '*', '', '');

