(61, 14, 1, '', '2018-10-29 02:54:29', 413, 6405, '9157242d928a9b7c840ba3f1815ba27bca14a340', '{\"id\":14,\"asset_id\":\"84\",\"title\":\"NDRRMC CONVENES IN PREPARATION FOR TYPHOON YUTU (I.N.)\",\"alias\":\"ndrrmc-convenes-in-preparation-for-typhoon-yutu-i-n\",\"introtext\":\"<h2 itemprop=\\\"name\\\" style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 12pt; color: #ff6600;\\\"><strong>NDRRMC CONVENES IN PREPARATION FOR TYPHOON YUTU (I.N.)<\\/strong><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size: 12pt; color: #ff6600;\\\"><strong><\\/strong><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size: 12pt; color: #000000;\\\"><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/ocd.gov.ph\\/images\\/OCD\\/PhotoRelease\\/PR1_1.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"PR1 1\\\" \\/><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span>\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0<\\/span>26 October 2018- National Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Council (NDRRMC) convened in preparation for Typhoon Yutu (international name) as it enters the Philippine Area of Responsibility (PAR) by 27 October 2018.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0 The Pre-Disaster Risk Assessment meeting was presided by NDRRMC Executive Director and Civil Defense Administrator Usec Ricardo B Jalad and attended by representatives from NDRRMC member agencies DSWD, DILG, NEDA, DOST-PAGASA, MGB, DepEd, PIA, DICT, NAMRIA, DBM, DOF, DPWH, PNP, BFP, AFP <g class=\\\"gr_ gr_24 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Punctuation only-ins replaceWithoutSep\\\" id=\\\"24\\\" data-gr-id=\\\"24\\\">and<\\/g> OCD CAR. The Regional DRRM Councils I<g class=\\\"gr_ gr_26 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Style replaceWithoutSep\\\" id=\\\"26\\\" data-gr-id=\\\"26\\\">,II<\\/g>, III, IVA, IVB <g class=\\\"gr_ gr_25 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Punctuation only-ins replaceWithoutSep\\\" id=\\\"25\\\" data-gr-id=\\\"25\\\">and<\\/g> V also joined the meeting via teleconference.<\\/p>\\r\\n\",\"fulltext\":\"\\r\\n<p><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/ocd.gov.ph\\/images\\/OCD\\/PhotoRelease\\/PR1_2.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"PR1 2\\\" width=\\\"699\\\" height=\\\"465\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0 According to PAGASA, Typhoon Yutu (I.N. has maintained its strength as it continues to move West of the Philippines at 25 km\\/h with maximum sustained winds of 185 km\\/h near the center and gustiness up to 225 km\\/h and a diameter of 800 km. As reported, TY Yutu is expected to enter the Philippine Area of Responsibility 27 October 2018. Hoisting of Tropical Cyclone Warning Signal (TCWS) is expected over Eastern section of Northern and Central Luzon on 28 October 2018 (Sunday). TY Yutu is expected will bring moderate to heavy rains over Northern and Central Luzon starting 29 October 2018.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0 DENR-MGB added that possible landslides may be experienced in some areas in the Eastern section of Northern Luzon.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0 Agencies under the response cluster presented preparedness measure for TY Yutu. Among the relative measures is the issuance of warning and advisories to the Local Government Units by the DILG; DSWD\\u2019s efforts for the stockpiling of food and non-food items; the prepositioning and stockpiling of medicines and <g class=\\\"gr_ gr_36 gr-alert gr_spell gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim ContextualSpelling\\\" id=\\\"36\\\" data-gr-id=\\\"36\\\">medicine<\\/g> supplies by DOH; AFP, PNP, BFP <g class=\\\"gr_ gr_33 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Punctuation only-ins replaceWithoutSep\\\" id=\\\"33\\\" data-gr-id=\\\"33\\\">and<\\/g> PCG have committed their response assets ready for deployment; and DPWH, DEPED <g class=\\\"gr_ gr_34 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Punctuation only-ins replaceWithoutSep\\\" id=\\\"34\\\" data-gr-id=\\\"34\\\">and<\\/g> DFA have activated respective units for the monitoring of the tropical cyclone.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/ocd.gov.ph\\/images\\/OCD\\/PhotoRelease\\/PR1_3.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"699\\\" height=\\\"465\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0 As of today, the NDRRM Operations Center is on <g class=\\\"gr_ gr_28 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Grammar only-ins replaceWithoutSep\\\" id=\\\"28\\\" data-gr-id=\\\"28\\\">WHITE<\\/g> alert status and will raise its alert status to BLUE on 28 October 2018 in order to closely monitor the possible effects of the current weather system and ensure <g class=\\\"gr_ gr_32 gr-alert gr_spell gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim ContextualSpelling\\\" id=\\\"32\\\" data-gr-id=\\\"32\\\">efficient<\\/g> coordination with the member agencies.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0 The public is being advised to monitor weather updates and bulletin provided by PAGASA. - End<\\/p>\",\"state\":1,\"catid\":\"10\",\"created\":\"2018-10-29 02:47:09\",\"created_by\":\"413\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2018-10-29 02:54:29\",\"modified_by\":\"413\",\"checked_out\":\"413\",\"checked_out_time\":\"2018-10-29 02:53:22\",\"publish_up\":\"2018-10-29 02:47:09\",\"publish_down\":\"0000-00-00 00:00:00\",\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"urls\":\"{\\\"urla\\\":false,\\\"urlatext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targeta\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlb\\\":false,\\\"urlbtext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlc\\\":false,\\\"urlctext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetc\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"